00:00:09.020 --> 00:00:14.000
Olek is a Polish-born Yarn artist living in
New York City that creates massive crocheted

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.610
installations like covering this train.

00:00:16.610 --> 00:00:21.800
It took two days and four assistants to complete
and is on display in Lodz, Poland.

00:00:21.800 --> 00:00:26.860
She's done several great installations with
yarn including The End is Far, The Animal

00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:29.430
Ball and the Crocheted Rickshaw.

00:00:29.430 --> 00:00:35.510
Sunset skateboard company makes LED-lighted
boards that last up to 100,000 hours.

00:00:35.510 --> 00:00:40.100
No batteries are required because the lights
are powered by the motion of the wheels.

00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:44.760
They give you the option to pick one of their
designs like the Ghost or the Wave or just

00:00:44.760 --> 00:00:45.930
build your own.

00:00:45.930 --> 00:00:50.430
Artist Brian Dettmer made these awesome skeleton
sculptures from melted cassette tapes including

00:00:50.430 --> 00:00:53.400
a bird, elk and bull skulls.

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:59.360
He also made these human skulls named after
the tapes used to make them such 80's metal,

00:00:59.360 --> 00:01:00.360
and women of pop.

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:04.309
He has many more amazing sculptures so be
sure to check out his website for more.

00:01:04.309 --> 00:01:09.240
The Archibird Cage Table was created by French
designer Gregoire De Lafforest.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:13.600
And the main part of the cage is attached
underneath the table and clear viewing tubes

00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:18.420
protrude though the top giving the birds the
ability to fly up into them and become part

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:20.180
of the tabletop decoration.

